{
  "doc_id": "24989",
  "text": "Besides electrospraying technique, graphene is employed as the Pt support to form a novel electrode structure in this study. Although commercial carbon blacks have been regarded as the most extensively used support for Pt, other supports including carbon nanotubes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and their composites with conducting polymers [CITATION_4] , carbon xerogel and carbon aerogel [CITATION_5] , carbon nanofibers [CITATION_6] , and graphene [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] have been utilized previously. Unsupported Pt nanoparticles were also employed as the catalysts for fuel cells as well [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] .",
